author: Katy Burne
title: SEC’s Mary Jo White Urges Review of Treasury Trading Venue Rules
text:
The chairwoman of the Securities and Exchange Commission, Mary Jo White, said in a speech Tuesday that the SEC could potentially subject government bond markets and their trading venues to new forms of oversight.
She noted that regulators should waste no time building on their understanding and responses to recent disruptive trading in U.S. Treasurys.
In a keynote speech on day one of a Federal Reserve Bank of New York event...
